and to permit persons to whom the Software is furnished to do so, strictly subject
to compliance with the Ethical Use Requirements set forth in Section 2.


2. ETHICAL USE REQUIREMENTS AND PROHIBITED USES

2.1 General Principle
The Software is designed and intended solely to increase safety, accountability,
transparency, and human control over artificial intelligence systems. Any use
inconsistent with this purpose is prohibited.

2.2 Prohibited Uses
Licensee shall NOT, and shall NOT permit any third party to, use the Software to:

    (a) SURVEILLANCE AND PRIVACY VIOLATIONS
        (i)   Develop, operate, or facilitate mass surveillance systems;
        (ii)  Implement social credit or social scoring systems;
        (iii) Enable pervasive tracking of individuals without their express,
              informed, and freely-given consent;
        (iv)  Process personal data in violation of applicable data protection
              laws or in ways that violate reasonable privacy expectations;

    (b) MILITARY AND WEAPONS APPLICATIONS
        (i)   Develop or operate autonomous weapons systems;
        (ii)  Develop or operate lethal autonomous systems or AI-directed
              targeting systems;
        (iii) Integrate the Software into military command and control systems
              for kinetic operations;

    (c) DISCRIMINATION AND CIVIL RIGHTS VIOLATIONS
        (i)   Make decisions affecting hiring, credit, housing, insurance, or
              criminal justice that unlawfully discriminate based on race, color,
              religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, genetic information,
              or other protected characteristics under applicable law;
        (ii)  Suppress, censor, or restrict lawful speech or expression;
        (iii) Target individuals or groups for persecution, harassment, or
              differential treatment based on protected characteristics;
        (iv)  Implement policies that systematically disadvantage protected groups;

    (d) MANIPULATION AND EXPLOITATION
        (i)   Deceive, manipulate, or exploit vulnerable populations including
              children, elderly persons, or individuals with cognitive disabilities;
        (ii)  Deploy dark patterns, manipulative interfaces, or deceptive practices
              to obtain consent or influence behavior;
        (iii) Create addictive systems designed to exploit psychological vulnerabilities;

    (e) AUTHORITARIAN CONTROL
        (i)   Develop or operate systems designed to suppress democratic processes,
              free elections, or political participation;
        (ii)  Enable censorship regimes or information control systems;
        (iii) Facilitate social manipulation at population scale for political purposes;
        (iv)  Support regimes engaged in crimes against humanity, genocide, or
              systematic human rights violations;

    (f) SUBVERSION OF SAFETY SYSTEMS
        (i)   Bypass, disable, or undermine safety controls, guardrails, or
              governance mechanisms in AI systems;
        (ii)  Facilitate "jailbreaking" or circumvention of safety measures for
              malicious purposes;
        (iii) Remove or disable audit logging, accountability mechanisms, or
              transparency features;

    (g) PRIMARY HARM
        (i)   Develop systems whose primary, substantial, or intended purpose is
              to cause physical harm, psychological harm, economic harm, or
              reputational harm to individuals or groups;
        (ii)  Use the Software in bad faith under the pretext of "research,"
              "testing," or "academic purposes" when the true intent is to
              develop harmful applications.

2.3 Safe Harbor for Security Research
Nothing in Section 2.2(f) shall prohibit good-faith security research, vulnerability
disclosure, red-teaming, or adversarial testing conducted for the purpose of
improving system safety, provided that:
    (i)   Such research is conducted ethically and responsibly;
    (ii)  Findings are disclosed to affected parties and/or the public in
          accordance with responsible disclosure practices;
    (iii) The research does not itself cause substantial harm.


3. PERMITTED USES

The following uses are expressly permitted and encouraged:

    (a) Developing, deploying, or operating AI agent systems in commercial,
        governmental, research, or personal contexts where the purpose is to
        increase safety, accountability, or human control;

    (b) Preventing AI systems from causing accidental or negligent harm through
        policy enforcement, constraint checking, or runtime governance;

    (c) Conducting legitimate security research, penetration testing, red-teaming,
        or adversarial evaluation to improve AI safety;

    (d) Academic research into AI safety, AI governance, AI alignment, or related fields;

    (e) Building compliance systems, audit systems, or regulatory technology for
        AI accountability;

    (f) Educational use, training, skill development, or demonstration purposes;

    (g) Any use that materially increases transparency, safety, human agency, or
        democratic control over AI systems.


