5.1 Upon request by the copyright holder, Licensee shall provide written
certification of compliance with the Ethical Use Requirements.

5.2 Licensee shall maintain records sufficient to demonstrate compliance with
this License for a period of no less than three (3) years.


6. LICENSE TERMINATION

6.1 Automatic Termination
This License and all rights granted hereunder shall automatically terminate,
without notice, upon Licensee's breach of any Ethical Use Requirement set forth
in Section 2.

6.2 Effect of Termination
Upon termination:
    (a) Licensee shall immediately cease all use of the Software;
    (b) Licensee shall destroy all copies of the Software in Licensee's possession
        or control;
    (c) Licensee shall certify in writing to the copyright holder that such
        destruction has been completed;
    (d) All sublicenses granted by Licensee shall also terminate;
    (e) The copyright holder reserves all legal and equitable remedies.

6.3 Survival
Sections 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, and 9 shall survive termination of this License.

6.4 Severability of Termination
Termination of this License with respect to one Licensee shall not affect the
rights of any other Licensee in good standing.


